This is a multiple choice question. It allows only one of the listed choices to be selected. An "Other" response type is shown as one of the choices below. This "other" response type is indicated by adding the "other" question parameter to this question and setting it equal to the value of the choice.

This is a multiple select question. It is very similar to a multiple choice question, but more than one choice can be selected at the same time. The "None" choice will remove all other selected boxes. This behavior is created by adding the "exclusive" question parameter and setting it equal to the value for that choice

This is a text question for entering any type of short, free-text responses. The text_area variant is designed to handle longer, multi-paragraph responses. Both of these question types can accept data entry from barcodes and QR codes. This behavior is enabled by adding the "allow_barcode" parameter. The barcode scanner currently only works on mobile devices.

This is a roster question type. It is used for more than one free-text response. Some use cases include, children's names and birthdays, pets names, barcodes, etc. This question type can also have barcode entry enabled.

The standout feature of Trellis its ability to map social networks. Edges between respondents are collected using the relationship question type and by asking "Name generator" questions designed to find out who a respondent has connections with. Here we've limited the number of respondents that can be listed to a minimum of 2 and maximum of 5.
